In summary

  • Statistical models for UKCP18’s 12km output seem to mimic the output well
  • Conditional simulations also seem to give sensible temperatures
  • CMIP6’s ScenarioMIP via CSIRO’s ACCESS-CSM2 output gives temperatures consistent with UKCP18’s for RCP8.5
  • Conditional simulations using CMIP6 captures its trends
  • Models for precipitation and wind speeds also seem to work, but need some refinement

Questions?

  • If we do things separately by month, how do we make coherent transitions between months?
  • How do we also ensure day-to-day consistency?
  • Are these important, as we’re looking as tree growth over ~60 years, and are conditioning on coherent data?
